==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spartan
<hw>Spar"tan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Spartanus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to Sparta, especially
to ancient Sparta; hence, hardy; undaunted; <as>as, <ex>Spartan</ex>
souls; <ex>Spartan</ex> bravey.</as></def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A
native or inhabitant of Sparta; figuratively, a person of great courage
and fortitude.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- marked by avoidance of luxury or comfort; spare, simple; marked
by self-denial -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sparteine</ent>⟦br⟧
